
1. Cashews grow on the ends of cashew fruit, the latter of which is commonly
used to make wine in Guinea-Bissau.
2. Unlike most civilizations and cultures, Guinea-Bissau has a matriarchal
society where women are in positions usually preferred for men.
3. To differentiate itself from its nearby country of Guinea, the name
was changed to Guinea-Bissau, despite not neighboring it.
4. Since it was colonized by Portugal, the official language of Guinea-Bissau
is a distinct Portuguese-based creole that is only spoken in this country.
5. Due to many factors, like a lack of education, drug trafficking,
political instability, and more, people live on an average of ~$2 a day.
6.